  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NGO Support / Literacy and Language Training for Adult Refugees</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The immediate objective of the project is to contribute towards increased self-reliance of refugees as a consequence of an improved education level. The project organises FAL training in Kyaka II refugee communities. Literacy and numeric skills combined with improved ability to analyse the environment and living conditions are expected to increase refugee&apos;s self-esteem and capacity to actively take efforts to improve their living standards. In addition English, French, business and civic training will be organised.</narrative>
  </description>
